    "en": {
      "title": "10 people arrested in Kurusapadu beach",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "These ten people were arrested during a special search operation carried out by the Sri Lankan Navy yesterday (16) night in Thalaimannar Kurusapadu sea area.",
        "Navy. The Navy carries out routine patrolling and search operations covering the country's sea and coastline to prevent illegal activities carried out in sea lanes.",
        "In this case, a dinghy that was traveling in a suspicious manner was surrounded by a Sri Lankan P175 coastal patrol vessel.",
        "At that time, four (04) men above 18 years of age, two women (02) and four below 18 years of age who operated the dinghy were arrested.",
        "Those arrested by the navy have been identified as belonging to Besalai, Urumalai, Kilinochchi and Kandalai. Thalaimannar was handed over to the police for further legal action.",
        "The Sri Lankan Navy has issued a statement in this regard, asking the public to avoid being caught in human trafficking organized by traffickers using unsafe vessels to earn money, trying to migrate illegally from the country and risking their lives to avoid being punished before the law."
      ],
